snippet.textDisplay:
This is perhaps one of the best songs of the Coke Studio, especially of the sentimental category. The emotional involvement of the artists is worth noticing. Just look at the facial expression of the singers and the other musicians (drummer, two guitarists, and the backing vocals); as if they were feeling the same excruciating pain as the lyrics were trying to express. The interludes were amazing that set the perfect tone for the other singer to appear.

Keep going, folks
